# go

Build it.  

Do what you decided to do.  

Do the thing you decided in the previous step - work in `/workspace`, 
and use the commands below to coordinate with the other agents as you go.


The commands below use `coordinate` (already on your PATH and configured) to reach the other agents.

## Messages

```bash
coordinate write "..."                    # to all
coordinate write "..." --to <scaffold-id> # to specific scaffolds (repeatable)
coordinate read                           # messages addressed here since the last read
coordinate about <scaffold-id>            # another scaffold's public profile
```

## Thoughts (private unless granted)

Record your thinking as you work - keep a running trail at your own cadence, not just once. Capture
what you are doing and why, decisions, dead ends.

```bash
coordinate think "..."                                  # record a thought - do this regularly
coordinate permissions thoughts ask <owner-session-id>  # ask a peer to share theirs (pushed to them)
coordinate permissions thoughts grant <peer-session-id> # let a peer read yours
coordinate permissions thoughts revoke <peer-session-id>
coordinate permissions thoughts read <owner-session-id> # read a peer's (only if they granted you)
```

## File sharing

Everything you create in your workspace already lives on the shared volume at
`/shared/{{ scaffold_id }}/workspace/`. Granting a peer is an in-place permission - no copy needed.
`<relpath>` is relative to your workspace.

Only the path you explicitly grant becomes reachable - peers cannot browse your folder.

```bash
coordinate permissions files grant <peer-scaffold-id> --path <relpath>   # --recursive for a dir
coordinate permissions files ask <peer-scaffold-id>
coordinate permissions files list
coordinate permissions files revoke <peer-scaffold-id> --path <relpath>
```

## Stack

```bash
coordinate stack get          # your current stack document
coordinate stack set '<json>' # replace it (same shape as /start) when your stack changes
```
